<p>I am using internationalization in jsf with jsp's using the below line:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;f:loadBundle var="lable" basename="com.infy.jcart.resources.Lang"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>On the jsp page I am displaying some commandLinks on clicking which the page will be translated to that language.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;h:form&gt;                 &lt;h:commandLink value="#{lable.English}" action="#{changeLocale.changeLangEng}"&gt;&lt;/h:commandLink&gt;&amp;nbsp;                 &lt;h:commandLink value="#{lable.Bengali}" action="#{changeLocale.changeLangBengali}"&gt;&lt;/h:commandLink&gt;&amp;nbsp;                 &lt;h:commandLink value="#{lable.Hindi}"   action="#{changeLocale.changeLangHindi}"&gt;&lt;/h:commandLink&gt;&amp;nbsp;                 &lt;h:commandLink value="#{lable.Kannada}" action="#{changeLocale.changeLangKannada}"&gt;&lt;/h:commandLink&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/h:form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But when I load the jsp page for the first time, only the link in English language is displayed properly, and other command links are dispayed as :</p>  <pre><code>???????? </code></pre>  <p>I have put the values for the keys in lang.properties file.</p>  <p>Once I refresh the browser page, other links are also displayed properly.</p>  <p>But why only for the first time the question marks appear for languages other than English ?</p>  <p>This is my properties file:</p>  <pre><code>English=English Hindi=\u0939\u093F\u0928\u094D\u0926\u0940 Bengali=\u09AC\u09BE\u0982\u09B2\u09BE Kannada=\u0C95\u0CA8\u0CCD\u0CA8\u0CA1 </code></pre>  <p>This is the managed bean class for changing locale:</p>  <pre><code>public String changeLangEng(){         return this.changeLang("en");     }      public String changeLangHindi(){         return this.changeLang("hi");     }      public String changeLangKannada(){         return this.changeLang("kn");     } public String changeLang(String loca){         locale=loca;         FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().getViewRoot().setLocale(new Locale(locale));         return "";     } </code></pre>